<span id="xx.ii-p5"></span>————————————

<span id="xx.ii-p6"></span><span class="c16"><span
id="xx.ii-p6.1"></span>I Wrote</span> again to the same persons <span
id="fr_3234"></span>[3235](#fn_3234.md) another treatise, which I entitled
*On Rebuke and Grace*, because I had been told that some one there had
said that no man ought to be rebuked for not doing God’s commandments,
but that prayer only should be made on his behalf, that he may do them.
This book begins on this wise, “I have read your letters, dearly beloved
brother Valentine.”

